cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use QuantCall in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "QuantCall: Benchmarking Tool-Calling Reliability Under Quantization"
authors:
  - family-names: "Happynood"
    given-names: "Alex"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-06-28"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Happynood/quant-toolcall-bench"
license: MIT
abstract: >
  QuantCall is a reproducible benchmark for measuring how quantization
  and inference backends degrade LLM function-calling and structured-output
  reliability. It produces structured metrics (SVR, TSA, AC, Abstention,
  FCR, ΔFCR, CDR, η) from real model runs with full reproducibility manifests.
